431 MUSCADET-SUR-LIE 1964, Barre 2.75 2.49 26.90 The lees is the heavy sediment which young wines throw in barrel. These are left behind when the wine is “racked” or transferred from one barrel to another. This Muscadet was slowly and carefully taken from the barrel by hand, not to disturb the sediment at the bottom. It is a costly process, and is wasteful of wine. However, the reward is a rich, intense, and exceedingly flavorsome Muscadet that will prove astonishingly good to many of you. Less than 100 cases were produced in this fashion.
